{
  "_comment": [
    "Example MCP client config (e.g. Claude Code / Claude Desktop) for the",
    "EarWitness local assistant tools. The client launches EarWitness as a",
    "stdio subprocess; EARWITNESS_MCP_STDIO=1 makes it boot Repo + the MCP",
    "server ONLY (no Phoenix endpoint, no desktop window) and speak JSON-RPC",
    "over stdin/stdout. See EarWitnessWeb.Application.start/2 and the",
    "anubis-mcp ADR. Access is off by default — enable it in EarWitness",
    "Settings first (it is instantly revocable there).",
    "",
    "PRODUCTION: point 'command' at the installed release binary (the path",
    "below is illustrative for a macOS app bundle). RELEASE stdout is clean",
    "JSON-RPC.",
    "",
    "DEV: you can instead use mix, but keep stdout clean — the JSON-RPC",
    "stream shares stdout, so route logs to stderr and silence compile noise:",
    "  \"command\": \"mix\",",
    "  \"args\": [\"run\", \"--no-halt\"],",
    "  \"env\": { \"EARWITNESS_MCP_STDIO\": \"1\", \"MIX_QUIET\": \"1\" },",
    "  \"cwd\": \"/absolute/path/to/desktop-example-app-main\"",
    "(compile the project once beforehand so no build output hits stdout)."
  ],
  "mcpServers": {
    "earwitness": {
      "command": "/Applications/EarWitness.app/Contents/MacOS/ear_witness",
      "args": ["start"],
      "env": {
        "EARWITNESS_MCP_STDIO": "1"
      }
    }
  }
}
